Package com.cafean.client.anim

Class AnimationModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.anim.AnimationModule
  • public abstract class AnimationModule
extends java.lang.Object
    The abstract base class for Animation Modules. These modules customize and control the process of retrieving data and converting it for proper display in an Animation Plug-in View.

      • getFileLabel

        public final java.lang.String getFileLabel()
        Returns the 'label' of the graphics file being animated using this module. This label may be null or zero-length if the default graphics file is being animated.

      • getDefaultFileLabel

        public java.lang.String getDefaultFileLabel()
        Returns the assumed default file label that should be used when animating with this module. Animation modules for job types that do not support multiple concurrent graphics files do not require this method.

      • getAppType

        public abstract java.lang.String getAppType()
        Returns the application type that this animation module supports. The application type is the unique string that identifies the type of task being animated.

        Parameters:

        public abstract int getNativeUnits​(DataSource source)

        Returns:

      • loadVolumeChannelNames

        public abstract java.lang.String[] loadVolumeChannelNames​(GeneralRange range,
                                                          java.lang.String[] channelNames,
                                                          java.lang.String volumeID)
        Load the channel names needed to map the given volume id to a set of channel names. The range given is used to determine the appropriate channel names to retrieve. For ranges of type GeneralRange.GENERIC the application type/pattern mapping is used to generate appropriate ids.
        Parameters:
        range - the GeneralRange used to animate the given volumes/channels.
        channelNames - a String[] to store the channel names list if it is the appropriate size.
        volumeID - a String containing the volume id to retrieve channel names for
        Returns:
        a String containing the requested channel names. This array should be channelNames if the array is the proper size.

      • loadVolumeChannelNames

        public java.lang.String[] loadVolumeChannelNames​(DataSource dataSource,
                                                 GeneralRange range,
                                                 java.lang.String[] channelNames,
                                                 java.lang.String volumeID)
        Loads the channel names needed to map the given volume id to a set of channel names. This default implementation simply calls loadVolumeChannelNames(GeneralRange, String[], String).
        Parameters:
        dataSource - the DataSource use to animate the given volumes/channels.
        range - the GeneralRange used to animate the given volumes/channels.
        channelNames - a String[] to store the channel names list if it is the appropriate size.
        volumeID - a String containing the volume id to retrieve channel names for
        Returns:
        a String containing the requested channel names. This array should be channelNames if the array is the proper size.
        See Also:
        loadVolumeChannelNames(GeneralRange, String[], String)

      • plotVariables

        public boolean plotVariables​(DataSource dataSource,
                             int dbid,
                             CalcServerRequester requester,
                             AcGraceIntf acgrace,
                             java.lang.String[] varNames,
                             boolean clear)
        Plots the given variable variables using the given AcGrace instance. The default behavior is to attempt to plot by loading the plot file directly. Modules that support plotting by directly retrieving data from the Calculation Server should implement that behavior by overriding this method.
        Parameters:
        dataSource - the DataSource handling the current connection
        dbid - the dbid of the currently active job for the given data source
        requester - the CalcServerRequester being used to communicate with the job
        acgrace - the AcGraceIntf instance to use in plotting the given variables
        varNames - a String[] containing the channel names of the variables to plot
        clear - true if the graph should be cleared before plotting the new data
        Returns:
        true if the variables were plotted, false otherwise

      • supportsCustomUnits

        public boolean supportsCustomUnits()
        Returns whether the code supports retrieving custom engineering units for individual jobs.
        Returns:
        a true for custom unit support, a false otherwise
